btrplace.plan.event

Class Action

  • java.lang.Object
    • btrplace.plan.event.Action
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Event
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Allocate, BootNode, BootVM, ForgeVM, KillVM, MigrateVM, ResumeVM, ShutdownNode, ShutdownVM, SuspendVM

    public abstract class Action
extends Object
implements Event
    An action is an event that has to be scheduled for reliability purpose.

    An action may embed several other events. Events are attach to the actions using Action.Hook. hook.

    Author:
    Fabien Hermenier

    • Method Detail

      • apply

        public boolean apply(Model i)
        Apply the action on a model. In practice, the events attached to Action.Hook.PRE are executed in first, then applyAction(btrplace.model.Model) is called. Finally, the events attached to Action.Hook.POST are executed.
        Specified by:
        apply in interface Event
        Parameters:
        i - the instance to alter with the action
        Returns:
        true if the action and all the events were applied successfully
